    "plan_content": "Here's the plan I've researched and documented. The implementation touches exactly 4 locations:\n\n---\n\n**1. `crates/uv-cli/src/lib.rs`** — Add `Stats(StatsArgs)` to `CacheCommand` enum + a new `StatsArgs` struct (identical shape to the existing `SizeArgs` with the same `--human/-H/--human-readable` flag).\n\n**2. `crates/uv/src/commands/cache_stats.rs`** *(new file)* — Implements `pub(crate) fn cache_stats(cache: &Cache, human_readable: bool, printer: Printer) -> Result<ExitStatus>`. Loops over `CacheBucket::iter()`, calls `cache.bucket(bucket)` to get each bucket's path, measures it with `diskus::DiskUsage`, prints `{bucket}: {size}` per line, then a `total:` line. Uses `human_readable_bytes` for the `--human` format. Non-existent bucket directories print `0`.\n\n**3. `crates/uv/src/commands/mod.rs`** — Add `mod cache_stats;` and `pub(crate) use cache_stats::cache_stats;` alongside the existing `cache_size` entries.\n\n**4. `crates/uv/src/lib.rs`** — Add one dispatch arm after `CacheCommand::Size`: `commands::cache_stats(&cache, args.human, printer)` — synchronous (no `.await`), no preview gating.\n\nKey notes from exploration:\n- `CacheBucket::iter()` yields 10 buckets (notably `Python` is excluded from the iterator — intentional per the codebase)\n- The `Display` impl for `CacheBucket` uses versioned names like `wheels-v6`, `sdists-v9`, etc.\n- No preview feature gating needed (unlike `cache_size` which warns about preview)",
